page.title: 10TOPOGRAPHY,ALTITUDE,CLIMATE
page.content:
{_TOPOGRAPHY_ Underlying rock exposed by deep cutting streams and past quarrying.Millstone grit and Culm measures/carboniferous. Rock overlaid with glacial deposits such as sand/gravel beds and glacial clays from the Lake district and Scotland.Podsols formed in the Piethorne area due to leaching of materials.
{_ALTITUDE_ Highest point 468m above sea level. Lowest point 233m above sea level. Average rainfall about 1500mm/year. Growing season is abour 7 to 8 months. Land description-Poor Agricultural, medium to poor grazing land.
{_C/5/10/7/85_
